 afterwards, and it contains too many nuts and unnecessary ingredients. But on the whole, it is a light meal for lazy summer days, and is particularly tasty with an alcoholic beverage of your preference!","rating":3,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/32532774?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"1001-books-to-read-before-you-die","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/32532774?shelf=1001-books-to-read-before-you-die"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2437329339"},"likeCount":102,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":26,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:1036893":{"id":1036893,"__typename":"User","legacyId":1036893,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1514061293i/1036893._UX200_CR0,54,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":894,"viewableName":"Fabian","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/1036893-fabian","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":1361},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.y2v63wYxNPaGj161RCEuZA":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.y2v63wYxNPaGj161RCEuZA","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.HSAdw_h85UV4sJKgqCtBQg"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:1036893"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1643485435920,"createdAt":1409857554000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1550548556219,"text":"Will ever these tales of incest cease? Well, my true guess is no, for they sure do captivate (lookin' atchu V.C. Andrews [...R.I.P., girl]!). Another case in point: this early novel from major Nobel contender (I'm certain of this, right?) Ian McEwan. \"The Cement Garden\" is considered by critics to be \"Lord of the Flies\"-like in its plot structure and because it contains young protagonists. But I must venture to say that it mostly resembles an early version of Bertolucci's \"Dreamers\" (of course by that I mean its novel predecessor)-- this is similarly an enchanted but truly megagrueling experience. After \"Atonement\", \"Cement Garden\" takes second place in the Maestro of English Prose's impressive (though... inconsistent) repertoire.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/1036893?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1045449109"},"likeCount":99,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":7,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:8686221":{"id":8686221,"__typename":"User","legacyId":8686221,"imageUrlSquare":"","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":116,"viewableName":"Wen","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/8686221-wen","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":37},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.H1l7YrpFFTuNVL-I7xYNXg":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.H1l7YrpFFTuNVL-I7xYNXg","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.HSAdw_h85UV4sJKgqCtBQg"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:8686221"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1642496482156,"createdAt":1515333413000,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1515333564000,"text":"This was McEwan’s very first novel, which earned him the fame and the nickname Ian Macabre. It was narrated by a 15-year-old boy on his life with his three young siblings in a secluded big house shortly after the death of both parents. They grew up in an isolated and dysfunctional family. The lack of adult supervision and sexual experiences, and the yearning for kinship while desiring individual space, led them to explorations and experiments that beyond inexplicable. \u003cbr /\u003eIt was haunting and disturbing to say the least. Comparing 